		<p><h1>The Panmultimedia story</h1></p>
		<p>This lead article briefly describes the panmultimedia story and what we hope to achieve by sharing Panmultimedia.com with the global internet community. </p>
		<p><br></p>
		<p>Panmultimedia.com was created by a New Zealand–based Company called Pansophy Limited specialising in contract research and the creation of online teaching and learning spaces. Pansophy Limited became a registered Company in 2005 and has a published, contract research history in transdisciplinary science. </p>
		<p><br></p>
		<p>Our aim in creating Panmultimedia is to make this website an online library of digital multimedia that supports the growing digital resource needs of educators, students, researchers, communicators and creative people. This site adds a further node to an existing online network of amazing digital multimedia resources that are now available worldwide. Panmultimedia digital multimedia resources may be used under the terms and conditions of Creative Commons licensing. Licenses are also available for those wanting to use Panmultimedia digital resources in commercial applications.</p>
		<p><br></p>
		<p><h1>Context</h1></p>
		<p>The rapid development of computer and Internet technology has created a unique opportunity for the creation of online teaching and learning environments, resources and technologies. Creative online learning spaces of this kind have the potential to dramatically change the theory, practice and outcomes of education as we currently know them. An opportunity currently exists to contribute towards a revolution in education.</p>
		<p><br></p>
		<p><h1>Panmultimedia.com</h1></p>
		<p>We have chosen to focus on the development of computer based teaching and learning environments, resources and technologies in order to meet the needs of a rapidly growing global internet community. Providing online access to a comprehensive collection and international network of digitial multimedia content is a developmental priority in the creation of online, computer-based teaching and learning. Pansophy Limited, the parent Company of Panmultimedia is commited to technological innovation that will see the use of online educational technologies in a new and rapidly changing social networking context.</p>
		<p><h1>First step in a long journey</h1></p>
		<p>As panmultimedia goes online in February 2013 we have uploaded our the very first collections of digital photographs, video, photographic clipart and artwork. In addition to this we are curently preparing further digital collections and new types of media that we hope will soon be available. </p>
		<p><br></p>
		<p>Anthony and Rhonda Cole</p>
		<p>Directors (Pansophy Limited)</p>
		
